<title>UK: UK's Northern Rock says MD Sharp has died.</title>
<headline>UK's Northern Rock says MD Sharp has died.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Northern Rock Building Society said on Thursday that its managing director Christopher Sharp died suddenly this morning.</p>
<p>Chairman Robert Dickinson said Leo Finn, Sharp's deputy, has been appointed managing director with immediate effect.</p>
<p>&quot;It was Chris' greatest desire that Northern Rock complete its conversion to Plc status on schedule and to plan and so remain a vibrant, independent force based in the northeast of England. This is precisely what will now take place,&quot; Dickinson said in a statement.</p>
<p>The society, whose members have approved plans to convert itself into a bank, is expected to float on the London stock exchange on October 1.</p>
